This paper deals with question answering tasks using distributed vector representation, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves logical reasoning and common-sense inference, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of Tensor Product Representation (TPR) suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
